 (also called James), and his grandson Charles (‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’) made various unsuccessful attempts to recover the English throne. Their supporters were known as Jacobites (from Latin <i>Iacobus</i>), and the name James became for a while particularly associated with Roman Catholicism on the one hand, and Highland opposition to the English government on the other. Nevertheless, it has since become one of the most perennially popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir James Bradshaigh KN was born about 1378, in Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Anne Prescott. He died in 1425, in his hometown, at the age of 48."},"et":{"about 1378–1425":"umbes 1378–1425","1382–Female":"1382–Surnud","1408–1446":"1408–1446","1378–1425":"1378–1425","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","1378":"1378","about 1378":"umbes 1378","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","Haigh, Wigan, Lancashire, England":"Wigan, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1378–1425":"noin 1378–1425","1382–Female":"1382–Kuollut","1408–1446":"1408–1446","1378–1425":"1378–1425","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","1378":"1378","about 1378":"noin 1378","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","Haigh, Wigan, Lancashire, England":"Wigan, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1378–1425":"environ 1378–1425","1382–Female":"1382–Décédée","1408–1446":"1408–1446","1378–1425":"1378–1425","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","1378":"1378","about 1378":"environ 1378","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","Haigh, Wigan, Lancashire, England":"Wigan, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Halton, Cheshire, England":"Halton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir James Bradshaigh KN est né environ 1378, à Wigan, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Anne Prescott. Il est décédé en 1425, dans sa ville n